HEADWORD: fledged
<hw>fledged</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having developed
feathers or plumage; often used in combination; -- of birds.</def>
[Narrower terms: <stype>fledgling(prenominal),
fledgeling(prenominal)</stype>] <ant>unfledged</ant>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mature.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>equipped with feathers; -- of an arrow.</def>⟦br⟧
